[1
Date: 11 Mar 2001
From: Pig Disease Information Centre <pdic@btinternet.org>
Source: BBC radio and MAFF [edited

The largest daily toll so far is today with 25 outbreaks, bringing the
total to 164, which includes 1 in Northern Ireland. Others include: Kent
and Gloucestershire infected for [the first time; other outbreaks were in
Powys, Devon (4), Cumbria (8), Worcestershire, Derbyshire, Dumfries and
Galloway (2), Tyne and Wear, Co. Durham (2) and Herefordshire.
The Gloucestershire outbreak is in the Forest of Dean where sheep roam
freely over large areas.
As the tourist season gets underway, there is concern about the effects
on the tourist industry.
[The Minister of Agriculture reiterated today the disease is under control
and
that vaccination is not an option.
More information is posted at <http://www.pighealth.com>
